5. Context Engine Integration
Add a new branch to lib/context-engine/evaluate.ts:
When maturity_state = DRAFT or PRE_TRIP_STRUCTURED, and user_profiles.preferences.budget_intelligence exists, and the trip has destination(s) with known regional cost data:
• If lodging_per_night_cap is set and regional average exceeds it: surface nudge in the pre_trip context state: “Your lodging target may be tight for {destination} during {season}. Consider nearby alternatives or adjusting your budget for this trip.”
• If total_daily_target is set and destination is a known high-cost area: surface nudge: “{Destination} tends to run above your daily target. The platform will help you find options that fit.”
This is a new branch in the existing evaluate() function, NOT a new context state. It fires within the existing pre_trip state. If no budget data exists (most users initially), the branch is a no-op — zero output, no error.
If budget data is malformed (corrupted JSONB), fail silently with a console.warn and skip the budget branch. Never crash the context engine because of bad budget data.
6. Voice Capture Enhancement (PLANNED — document, do not build yet)
In a future pass, the voice parse route should detect budget statements across all context types (not just signal_capture). Patterns to detect: “I don’t want to spend more than $X”, “My budget is $X a day”, “I’d rather not go over $X for flights.”
When detected, the system should ask: “Should I remember this for future trips, or just this one?” and route to profile or trip-level storage accordingly.
This is documented here for completeness. The first prompt implements the preferences page and context engine integration only.
7. API Routes
Route	Method	Purpose
/api/account/budget	GET	Returns budget_intelligence from user_profiles.preferences. Returns { budget: BudgetIntelligence | null }.
/api/account/budget	PATCH	Updates budget_intelligence. Merges into preferences JSONB. Emits budget_preferences_updated. Returns { budget }.
8. FOCL Registration
Feature ID: F-6.7.4. Phase: 2. Default enabled: false. No hard dependencies. Soft dependency: voice parse (for future voice capture).
When F-6.7.4 is inactive: Account page does not show “Budget preferences” row. Context engine budget branch does not fire. Trip Spark does not show budget estimates.
9. Governance Events
budget_preferences_updated — { account_id, fields_changed (array of field names that changed) }
budget_override_set — { trip_id, account_id, fields_overridden }
budget_signal_captured — { account_id, source_context (voice context type), signal_text, layer (profile/trip) } — future, when voice capture is built
10. Stress Behavior
Under PROTECTIVE: budget preferences remain readable and editable. Budget-aware context nudges continue to fire (they’re client-side evaluation, no external API dependency). Budget is purely profile data — no degradation expected.
11. Test Obligations
E2E (tests/e2e/budget-intelligence.spec.ts):
• Navigate to /account/preferences/budget → page loads with empty fields
• Set lodging cap = 200, food = 65, save → toast confirms → reload → values persist
• Clear all fields, save → budget is null → context engine budget branch is no-op
• Set budget, create trip with high-cost destination → verify context nudge appears (requires mock regional cost data or a known expensive destination)
Contract: budget data is account-scoped — user B cannot read user A’s budget via API.
12. §9a Dependency Declaration
• Trip workspace: NO (budget surfaces on account, not trip workspace directly in v1)
• Readiness: NO
• Right Now / context: YES — new branch in evaluate.ts for budget-aware pre_trip nudge. Risk: if budget JSONB is null or malformed, branch must be no-op. Never crash context engine.
• FOCL / activation: YES — feature_registry entry.


